01:34.720 --> 01:37.996
You take your nanny skiing,
the cost mounts up.

01:38.080 --> 01:40.071
So leave her at home.

01:40.160 --> 01:41.354
You still have to pay her.

01:41.440 --> 01:43.510
On holiday, you want your nanny most.

01:43.600 --> 01:45.514
But they see it as their holiday, too.

01:45.820 --> 01:48.754
Gabrielle even wanted us
to pay for a lift pass.

01:48.840 --> 01:51.274
In a ski resort, what else can you do?

01:51.360 --> 01:53.749
But you pay for flights, accommodation,
food...

01:53.840 --> 01:55.671
Actually, we didn't pay for food.

01:55.760 --> 01:57.955
Nannies make whatever demands they want.

01:58.040 --> 02:01.350
You don't want to go to the trouble
of finding a replacement.

02:01.440 --> 02:03.874
And the children get attached to them.

02:04.960 --> 02:06.518
Psst. Karen.

02:10.160 --> 02:12.071
What are you doing?

02:12.160 --> 02:14.071
Who are these people?

02:14.160 --> 02:16.230
They are our friends.

02:16.320 --> 02:17.912
What does that say about you?

02:18.640 --> 02:19.789
Sorry?

02:20.680 --> 02:22.591
Look at them.

02:22.680 --> 02:25.797
Is it something they put in the water
makes them stupid?

02:25.880 --> 02:28.155
I mean, take James here.

02:31.920 --> 02:33.876
He earns what? Six figures.

02:34.400 --> 02:36.789
Begrudges his nanny a living wage.

02:38.840 --> 02:42.435
His wife, Natasha...hangs on his every word.

02:42.520 --> 02:46.798
You wouldn't think
she has a degree in economics, would you?

02:48.360 --> 02:50.112
David...

02:51.160 --> 02:53.230
Well, David's David, isn't he?

02:54.360 --> 02:56.430
Just wants everyone to get on.

03:01.600 --> 03:03.511
Laura...

03:03.600 --> 03:05.795
Didn't you go backpacking with her once?

03:06.630 --> 03:09.755
We stayed in an
ashram in India together.

03:09.840 --> 03:14.630
Well, unless it's become part of the
Hilton chain, she won't be going back.

03:15.480 --> 03:16.799
Mark.

03:16.880 --> 03:20.156
Barely said a word all night,
which is probably just as well.

03:20.240 --> 03:22.800
It's about the only thing he's got
going for him.

03:22.880 --> 03:26.475
I mean, look at him.
Middle-aged, going on dead.

03:28.040 --> 03:29.553
Finally...

03:29.640 --> 03:31.437
You, Karen.

03:31.520 --> 03:32.873
What about me?

03:32.960 --> 03:35.633
When you were young,
you wanted to be outstanding.

03:35.720 --> 03:37.631
I've got news for you.

03:37.720 --> 03:39.472
You don't stand out at all.

03:40.520 --> 03:42.795
In fact, you fit right in.

03:49.320 --> 03:51.231
&1,5oo.

03:51.320 --> 03:54.153
It'll be worth double that in a few years.

03:54.240 --> 03:56.879
Would you excuse me a minute, please?

03:59.200 --> 04:02.237
Has anyone been to that new restaurant
on Deansgate?

04:02.320 --> 04:04.231
Yes. Marvellous.

04:04.320 --> 04:05.673
Help.

04:05.760 --> 04:07.671
What's the matter?

04:07.760 --> 04:09.352
I thlnk I've died and gone to hell.

04:09.440 --> 04:10.509
Worse, actually.

04:10.600 --> 04:13.672
I'm still here and this is my life.
Where are you?

04:13.760 --> 04:15.432
Bar Nexus.
- Can I come?

04:15.520 --> 04:17.829
But I thought you were having
a dinner party.

04:17.920 --> 04:20.387
Yeah, but I'm not sure I can stand it.

04:20.480 --> 04:22.550
You know the best way to handle that.

04:22.640 --> 04:25.393
Rachel, I'm already pissed.
- Well, then, roll a joint.

04:25.480 --> 04:27.391
I tell you, I wouId if I had any dope.

04:27.480 --> 04:31.439
You might just find a stray spliff
in my bedside table.

04:31.520 --> 04:33.431
Second drawer down.

04:33.520 --> 04:35.431
Seriously?
- Yeah, I'm serious.

04:35.520 --> 04:38.512
I knew I could rely on you. Thanks.
- No problem.

04:38.600 --> 04:40.192
Bye.

04:41.240 --> 04:44.516
I love auctions.
There's always the chance to find a bargain.

04:44.600 --> 04:48.832
Last week I stumbled on a painting and
I think it might be by the Norwich School.

04:48.920 --> 04:51.957
Well, it's of a Norwich School!

04:52.040 --> 04:54.315
Karen, you studied art history.

05:01.920 --> 05:05.196
Oh, I'm awfully sorry.
Would anybody like some?

05:05.920 --> 05:08.718
I've got to be up early.
- I don't, thanks.

05:13.560 --> 05:15.073
Were you out of your mlnd?

05:15.160 --> 05:17.720
Briefly. I don't think it was
very good stuff.

05:18.720 --> 05:20.790
I've never been so embarrassed.

05:20.880 --> 05:24.236
School nativity play -
one of the Three Wise Men wet themselves.

05:24.320 --> 05:25.958
Your mother told me.

05:26.040 --> 05:28.634
You do not offer marijuana
at dinner parties.

05:28.720 --> 05:31.075
You offered Cuban cigars, which smell worse.

05:31.160 --> 05:33.116
Yeah, but they're not illegal.

05:33.200 --> 05:34.997
In America they are.

05:36.040 --> 05:38.156
I'm sorry, David, but I was bored.

05:38.240 --> 05:40.196
Bored bloody rigid.

05:40.280 --> 05:41.793
You were certalnly quiet.

05:41.880 --> 05:43.393
If you got more involved...

05:43.480 --> 05:46.552
I had no interest
in discussing nannies again.

05:46.640 --> 05:48.790
That isn't all we talked about.

05:48.880 --> 05:51.997
Or skiing, house prices or
private education.

05:53.040 --> 05:56.191
You could have started a conversation.
- David, I tried.

05:56.280 --> 05:58.191
Oh, yeah.

05:58.280 --> 06:00.271
There's a tribe in Borneo,

06:00.360 --> 06:04.114
where instead of shaking hands,
men masturbate one other.

06:12.920 --> 06:14.831
They'll never invite us back.

06:14.920 --> 06:17.275
Thank God. We won't have
to admire their antiques.

06:17.360 --> 06:19.828
What's got into you?
They're our friends.

06:20.680 --> 06:22.272
I know.

06:22.360 --> 06:24.590
I'll never be able to sleep tonight.

06:24.680 --> 06:26.432
You would if you'd only relax.

06:26.520 --> 06:28.078
How do you suggest I do that?

06:28.160 --> 06:29.912
I didn't finish it.

06:40.040 --> 06:42.110
Buongiorno.

06:45.720 --> 06:47.153
There you go.

06:47.240 --> 06:49.310
Look at that.

06:50.640 --> 06:52.710
I'll deal with him. You lie in.

06:52.800 --> 06:55.075
Blimey! What have I done to deserve this?

06:56.720 --> 06:59.029
Actually, Pete, what have you done?

06:59.120 --> 07:00.997
How do you mean?

07:01.080 --> 07:02.991
Joking.

07:03.080 --> 07:07.232
Come on. It's nice.
I feel a bit like a princess, eh!

07:08.280 --> 07:11.352
Anything for me?
- Yeah, there's a couple.

07:11.440 --> 07:13.431
There you go, love.
- Ta.

07:13.520 --> 07:15.272
Oh, no.
- What?

07:15.360 --> 07:17.271
It's from my old school.

07:17.360 --> 07:19.590
After them library books again?

07:27.840 --> 07:29.990
I've been invited to a reunion.

07:30.080 --> 07:32.230
Blimey, that makes me feel old.

07:32.320 --> 07:34.276
<i>Mmm. Class of '84.</i>

07:35.600 --> 07:37.158
Are you going to go?

07:37.240 --> 07:40.357
Of course I'm not going.
- Come on. It will be fun.

07:40.440 --> 07:44.956
What? Standing round with guys
who were wankers then and estate agents now?

07:45.040 --> 07:46.314
I don't think so.

07:46.440 --> 07:48.396
At least you aren't like them.

07:48.480 --> 07:50.436
That's what I really object to!

07:50.520 --> 07:53.637
''A chance to catch up with old mates.''
Bollocks!

07:53.720 --> 07:57.952
A chance to see who's doing better
or worse. I'm not playing.

07:58.040 --> 07:59.758
On principle?
- Yeah.

07:59.840 --> 08:02.400
Not because you'll suffer by comparison?

08:04.440 --> 08:06.351
Face it, Pete.

08:06.440 --> 08:08.795
I have nothing to show for my life.

08:09.840 --> 08:11.637
God, I'm not even divorced.

08:12.680 --> 08:14.796
I wonder if Amanda Wagstaff will go.

08:14.880 --> 08:18.395
Amanda?
- I bet you'd like to see her again.

08:18.480 --> 08:20.391
Yeah.

08:20.480 --> 08:22.755
Oh, yeah.

08:22.840 --> 08:24.831
Maybe I can meet her husband.

08:24.920 --> 08:26.990
Maybe she'll show photos of her children.

08:27.080 --> 08:29.150
She split up from her husband.

08:29.240 --> 08:32.515
So my mum says. Having an affair.
- The bollocks!

08:32.600 --> 08:34.716
Hang on. You don't know it was his fault.

08:34.799 --> 08:36.552
Phuh! Excuse me.

08:36.640 --> 08:38.995
You don't know what his marriage was like.

08:39.080 --> 08:40.991
But if he had an affair...

08:41.080 --> 08:44.152
Not strictly an affair.
He only slept with her once.

08:45.200 --> 08:48.158
Your mother's intelligence is very good.

08:49.000 --> 08:52.072
Yeah. Yeah.
Erm, so do you want to go, or what?

08:53.160 --> 08:55.116
Oh. How much is it?

08:56.160 --> 08:57.798
40 quid?

08:57.880 --> 09:00.030
Oh, that's for a double ticket.

09:00.120 --> 09:01.155
Double?

09:03.280 --> 09:05.589
Thanks for agreeing to meet me.

09:05.680 --> 09:09.309
I almost didn't,
after that scene in the restaurant.

09:09.400 --> 09:12.153
Then I thought maybe you wanted
to apologise.

09:12.240 --> 09:13.912
I do.

09:14.960 --> 09:16.916
Well, go on, then.

09:18.440 --> 09:20.396
I apologise.

09:21.400 --> 09:24.870
I'm sorry I had a go at you
and your boyfriend.

09:24.960 --> 09:26.598
With the emphasis on ''boy''.

09:29.640 --> 09:33.633
I was embarrassed - you know,
Lonely Hearts...

09:33.720 --> 09:35.233
Was that your first?

09:35.320 --> 09:36.833
God, and last.

09:36.920 --> 09:39.593
I mean, Callie was the best of the bunch.

09:39.680 --> 09:41.636
Look how that turned out.

09:42.960 --> 09:45.793
No, I think I'd rather embrace celibacy.

09:45.880 --> 09:48.030
Can you embrace celibacy?

09:48.120 --> 09:51.078
So long as it doesn't lead anywhere.

09:53.360 --> 09:56.591
Do you really want to spend your life
with someone called Callie?

09:57.960 --> 09:59.916
Whereas, Danny...

10:01.360 --> 10:03.476
Do you think we can be friends?

10:05.160 --> 10:07.071
I don't think we can.

10:07.160 --> 10:09.116
I'd like to be.

10:11.720 --> 10:13.950
Maybe see a movie once in a while.

10:14.040 --> 10:16.474
Meet at parties without embarrassment.

10:16.560 --> 10:17.879
Yeah.

10:17.960 --> 10:20.918
Invite each other to...school reunions.

10:21.000 --> 10:23.594
Yeah.
- So you'll come?

10:23.680 --> 10:26.274
To a movie?
- No, to a school reunion.

10:26.360 --> 10:28.271
Say you will. Say you will.

10:28.360 --> 10:31.193
I don't want to go on my own or take a date.

10:31.280 --> 10:33.589
Amanda will be there, my first girlfriend.

10:33.680 --> 10:35.910
Her marriage has just split up.

10:36.000 --> 10:37.513
Pete and Jen will be there.

10:38.560 --> 10:40.516
OK.

10:42.440 --> 10:43.793
Hiya.
- Hi.

10:43.880 --> 10:45.791
Hi.

10:45.880 --> 10:49.236
Are you ready?
- Yeah. We're going to the cinema.

10:50.280 --> 10:51.952
Do you want to come?

10:52.040 --> 10:53.951
No.

10:54.040 --> 10:56.838
I've got...something...to do.

10:56.920 --> 10:58.831
What are you going to see?

10:58.920 --> 11:00.148
King Of Comedy.

11:00.240 --> 11:02.674
De Niro. We enjoyed that one, didn't we?

11:21.160 --> 11:23.230
What are you doing after work?

11:23.320 --> 11:25.072
I meant to talk to you about that.

11:25.160 --> 11:27.071
Good.

11:27.160 --> 11:29.071
Pete. Pete, relax.

11:29.160 --> 11:32.675
People will think we're having
a meeting, not an affair.

11:32.760 --> 11:34.716
Hey, we're not...

11:35.960 --> 11:37.871
We're not having an affair.

11:37.960 --> 11:40.190
That's what I want to talk about.

11:40.280 --> 11:41.918
We...

11:42.960 --> 11:46.077
We slept together once. That's it, right?

11:46.160 --> 11:49.311
You're forgetting the following morning.

11:49.400 --> 11:52.073
Well, I only count it as th... as the...

11:52.160 --> 11:56.597
What happened when we went away
won't happen again, right?

11:56.680 --> 11:59.194
So, you...
- Post.

12:05.200 --> 12:08.476
So you've sorted out your problems
with Jenny?

12:08.560 --> 12:10.630
Yes. Yes, I'm taking steps to.

12:10.720 --> 12:12.631
Have you spoken to her?

12:12.720 --> 12:14.631
That's the next step.

12:16.720 --> 12:18.995
Pete Gifford's phone.
- Hello.

12:19.080 --> 12:22.072
Oh, hiya, Jenny. It's Amy. Yeah.

12:22.160 --> 12:25.470
Yeah, he's just here. I'll pass him on.
Hang on.

12:29.040 --> 12:31.918
Hi.
- Hiya, Jen. Yeah.

12:33.600 --> 12:36.592
The cheque? No, the cheque's by the phone.

12:37.640 --> 12:39.596
Listen, I erm...

12:40.640 --> 12:42.471
I might have to work late tonight.

12:42.560 --> 12:44.471
OK.

12:44.560 --> 12:46.471
About eight. Yeah.

12:46.560 --> 12:48.471
Right.

12:48.560 --> 12:50.596
Eight thirty. Thereabouts.

12:51.880 --> 12:55.190
OK.
- OK.

12:56.440 --> 12:59.000
See you, love. Bye.
- See you later, yeah?

13:21.680 --> 13:25.434
How the hell did I manage
to accumulate so much tat?

13:25.520 --> 13:28.239
Shopping, I'd imagine.
- Well, it's time it went.

13:28.320 --> 13:32.598
If you saw a woman wearing this,
what would you think?

13:32.680 --> 13:34.636
That her husband's rich.

13:34.720 --> 13:36.358
Or she is.

13:36.440 --> 13:39.796
Either way, that she is impressed by wealth.
Well, I am not so shallow.

13:39.880 --> 13:42.474
You really hated that dinner party.

13:42.560 --> 13:44.869
No. It helped me see things clearly.

13:44.960 --> 13:48.794
I've become the sort of woman
I used to despise. It was a revelation.

13:48.880 --> 13:52.316
Like an out-of-body experience.
- Had you had the dope by then?

13:52.400 --> 13:56.029
I wanted to grab each of those people,
shake them and scream,

13:56.120 --> 14:00.750
''For God's sake, wake up, take a look at
yourselves before it's too late.''

14:01.760 --> 14:03.113
Isn't that Prada?

14:03.200 --> 14:05.953
Can you tell?
- Yeah.

14:07.000 --> 14:08.956
Wait, wait! I'll have it.

14:11.600 --> 14:13.556
You could take it up.

14:14.320 --> 14:16.151
You can't take up Prada.

14:16.240 --> 14:19.869
I want to strip away my life,
cut through all the crap

14:19.960 --> 14:22.918
and get back to the real me.
I've become so conformist!

14:23.000 --> 14:26.515
You have dope in your bedside table.
I have Joanna Trollope.

14:26.600 --> 14:28.238
Yeah, but it's Danny's.

14:28.320 --> 14:31.915
You get distracted by bullshit.
Why you must have an Aga.

14:32.000 --> 14:36.198
What Caribbean island is in.
What colour's the latest black.

14:36.280 --> 14:37.474
Isn't it black?

14:37.560 --> 14:41.269
Who gives a shit? The chattering classes
who can't think themselves

14:41.360 --> 14:43.669
and rely on the media to form their views.

14:43.760 --> 14:45.637
Right...

14:45.720 --> 14:47.597
What's that?
- Nothing.

14:47.680 --> 14:49.591
Let's have a gander.

14:49.680 --> 14:51.636
You wouldn't approve.

14:52.640 --> 14:56.918
It's a questionnaire. ''Your boyfriend:
Hump him or dump him?''

14:57.000 --> 14:59.560
Oh, I love those things.
- Isn't it media bullshit?

14:59.640 --> 15:04.111
It's just a bit of fun. It's not like
you're taking it seriously, is it?

15:04.200 --> 15:05.519
No, of course not.

15:05.600 --> 15:07.511
OK. Question one.

15:07.600 --> 15:09.750
''Sex.

15:09.840 --> 15:12.957
Is sex, A: something you're
keen to avoid?

15:13.040 --> 15:14.996
B: Willing to suffer?

15:15.720 --> 15:17.597
Or C: Gagging for more of?''

15:41.840 --> 15:43.796
C.

15:43.880 --> 15:46.030
Three points. Question two.

15:46.120 --> 15:49.590
''In the morning,
does your boyfriend bring you...

15:49.680 --> 15:51.477
A: The post?

15:51.560 --> 15:53.471
B: Fowers?

15:53.560 --> 15:55.516
Or C: Another orgasm?''

16:10.040 --> 16:11.951
All three.

16:12.040 --> 16:13.951
Fantastic.

16:14.040 --> 16:15.951
OK.

16:16.040 --> 16:17.951
Three, four, five, six.

16:18.040 --> 16:19.473
Are you sure you need to do it all?

16:19.560 --> 16:21.471
I know. I know. It's just...

16:21.560 --> 16:22.709
Well, he's very young.

16:22.800 --> 16:25.030
Isn't that why he's scoring so well?

16:25.120 --> 16:27.111
Yeah, but so are his friends.

16:27.200 --> 16:30.909
It's a terrible waste,
but Richey Manic, he is dead.

16:31.000 --> 16:35.869
No way, man. He's alive and well. He's in
India. Crispin's seen him there.

16:35.960 --> 16:40.351
Crispin, Crispin...
- He's in the mud under the Severn Bridge.

16:40.440 --> 16:43.557
Oh, no. I did see his face in
a cloud formation.

16:43.640 --> 16:45.790
Your head's a cloud formation.

16:45.880 --> 16:49.111
When he disappeared,
part of me went with him.

16:51.320 --> 16:53.788
To Richey.
- To Richey, man.

16:55.000 --> 16:56.956
To Richey.

17:00.920 --> 17:02.911
OK, so his friends are awful.

17:03.000 --> 17:05.309
David's were when I first met him.

17:05.400 --> 17:08.278
But you are not going out with his friends
but Danny.

17:08.359 --> 17:10.589
Mmm. Who's fun and intelligent.

17:10.680 --> 17:12.477
And sex on legs.

17:13.319 --> 17:15.231
Yeah. Case closed.

17:15.319 --> 17:17.276
Horoscopes.

17:21.000 --> 17:22.911
Hiya, love. Sorry I'm late.

17:23.000 --> 17:25.036
Work dragged on, you know.

17:25.119 --> 17:27.270
It's all right. Are you hungry?

17:27.359 --> 17:29.430
No. I got a burger coming home.

17:29.520 --> 17:32.478
I would have rung, but I had to crack on
with the audit.

17:32.560 --> 17:34.437
Get it finished?

17:34.520 --> 17:36.875
No, no. One mistake leads to a hundred.

17:36.960 --> 17:39.838
I'll have to work a few more late nlghts.

17:41.920 --> 17:43.876
Poor, overworked fool.

17:55.080 --> 17:59.039
Weren't you bringing me breakfast?
- I don't want to be late for work.

17:59.120 --> 18:01.429
Danny, I'm your boss.
You don't have to worry.

18:05.400 --> 18:06.628
Look...

18:10.160 --> 18:11.639
We need to talk.

18:11.720 --> 18:15.269
He's dumped you? - That's where
'''We have to talk'' tends to lead.

18:15.360 --> 18:17.271
Why?

18:17.360 --> 18:19.316
It's your friends.

18:19.400 --> 18:21.311
Me?

18:21.400 --> 18:23.311
And David, Pete and Jenny.

18:23.400 --> 18:26.153
And Adam. He was never very keen on Adam.

18:26.240 --> 18:29.198
Yeah, well, Adam I can understand,
but what's wrong with us?

18:29.280 --> 18:31.111
Nothing, but...

18:31.200 --> 18:33.270
they're not my kind of people.

18:33.360 --> 18:37.831
You mean, they don't sit around
talking about Richey Manic.

18:37.920 --> 18:39.353
Would David even know who he was?

18:41.040 --> 18:43.474
You're not going out with them, but me.

18:43.560 --> 18:48.315
But friends are important. That's the people
who you want to spend time with.

18:48.400 --> 18:50.994
I don't want to spend time with yours.

18:51.080 --> 18:53.355
I...I'll change my friends.

18:53.440 --> 18:56.796
Excuse me!
- I didn't mean it. He caught me unawares.

18:56.880 --> 18:58.393
Anyway, I was going to dump him.

18:58.480 --> 19:00.391
That's rather ironic, Rachel.

19:00.480 --> 19:03.677
Still, at least it's not any
great loss, is it?

19:03.760 --> 19:05.876
Oh, come on.

19:05.960 --> 19:07.393
No-one likes being dumped.

19:08.440 --> 19:10.715
And he did have a beautiful body!

19:12.000 --> 19:14.798
You know what you should do
when you feel down...

19:14.880 --> 19:16.791
Spend a lot of money?

19:16.880 --> 19:18.836
Something wild.

19:27.080 --> 19:29.036
Hello.

19:35.920 --> 19:39.390
What about a heart wrapped in a scroll,
inscribed ''David''?

19:39.480 --> 19:41.835
What if we get divorced?
- Pessimist.

19:41.920 --> 19:43.911
Pragmatist.
- Or a death's head skull.

19:44.000 --> 19:46.275
