26:14.960 --> 26:16.871
My tattoo's still sore.

26:16.960 --> 26:20.953
He's going to be upset if he has to go
on his own. Please go.

26:21.040 --> 26:25.556
It's er, Sharman Cross School,
Alderbrook Road, Wythenshawe.

26:25.640 --> 26:28.438
I'm due to meet him in an hour. Please go.

26:29.480 --> 26:31.198
I hope you get this message.

26:38.400 --> 26:40.311
Blimey, it's a bit low-rent.

26:40.400 --> 26:42.470
Like something out of Carrie.

26:42.560 --> 26:44.437
I'm not happy with this name tag.

26:46.120 --> 26:49.157
Pond Scum - it wasn't my only
school nickname.

26:49.240 --> 26:51.196
What was your other one?

26:54.480 --> 26:56.436
Smegma.

26:58.760 --> 27:00.716
Hey!

27:02.200 --> 27:04.031
Great, they're coming over.

27:04.120 --> 27:05.473
Yeah.

27:05.560 --> 27:07.471
Hiya.

27:07.560 --> 27:09.516
Oh, hiya.

27:16.840 --> 27:18.432
Adam.

27:18.520 --> 27:21.557
Hey, Karen. Why are you here?
- Rach can't make it, so I came.

27:21.640 --> 27:25.428
Oh, great...
- I'm her stand-in.

27:25.520 --> 27:29.115
Great. Er...let's do it.

27:29.200 --> 27:30.758
What do I have to do, then?

27:30.840 --> 27:33.877
This girl, Amanda Wagstaff,
is gagging for it.

27:42.760 --> 27:45.479
Thanks for not saying anything to Jen.

27:51.240 --> 27:53.196
Oh, my God.

28:19.680 --> 28:20.510
Amanda.

28:20.600 --> 28:22.511
Adam.

28:22.600 --> 28:25.637
Oh, er...I wasn't sure you'd remember.

28:25.720 --> 28:27.995
Well, the name tag helped.

28:28.080 --> 28:29.308
Oh, yeah.

28:29.400 --> 28:31.118
Of course I remember you.

28:31.200 --> 28:32.838
How are you?
- I'm great.

28:32.920 --> 28:35.639
God, you look fantastic. How are you?

28:35.720 --> 28:37.676
Yeah. I'm fine.

28:38.720 --> 28:42.315
Who are you with?
- Tall blonde woman with Pete.

28:42.400 --> 28:44.960
With Pond Scum?
- Yeah.

28:45.040 --> 28:46.598
She's just a friend.

28:46.680 --> 28:48.716
Very attractive.

28:48.800 --> 28:50.711
Yeah...

28:50.800 --> 28:51.835
What about you?

28:51.920 --> 28:53.990
Yeah, I'm with a friend, as well.

28:54.080 --> 28:57.595
Jill. Oh, she's the girl talking
to Jamie Franks.

28:59.680 --> 29:01.432
Very attractive, too.

29:02.600 --> 29:05.194
I was sorry...
- So what do you...

29:05.280 --> 29:07.510
Oh. Hmm.
- Go on. You first.

29:08.560 --> 29:11.438
I was sorry to hear about your marriage.

29:11.520 --> 29:13.033
That it was in trouble, I mean.

29:14.240 --> 29:17.471
It was in trouble, wasn't it?
- It's erm... It's over.

29:17.560 --> 29:19.630
Your husband had an affair.

29:19.720 --> 29:21.278
Where did you get that from?

29:21.360 --> 29:22.679
Pete's mum.

29:24.640 --> 29:26.870
It was me that had the affair.

29:26.960 --> 29:28.871
Oh. Is it still going on?

29:28.960 --> 29:30.279
No.

29:30.360 --> 29:34.512
No. I erm... I left her and now
I'm with Jill.

30:04.400 --> 30:06.595
Hey.
- Hey.

30:06.680 --> 30:09.638
God, no wonder I never got past first base.

30:09.720 --> 30:12.678
She's got two kids.
Her husband obviously did, then.

30:12.760 --> 30:16.036
Thanks for coming, Karen.
I think we can go now.

30:16.120 --> 30:18.031
No, it's only just started!

30:18.120 --> 30:20.076
Come with me.

30:32.480 --> 30:34.994
God, I can't believe this, you know.

30:35.080 --> 30:37.230
I used to sneak in here for a sly fag.

30:37.320 --> 30:39.470
15 years later, and I still do it.

30:39.560 --> 30:41.915
For God's sake, don't tell David.

30:42.960 --> 30:45.918
I'm good at keeping secrets. Don't worry.

30:46.000 --> 30:48.230
No, nothing. It doesn't matter.

30:48.320 --> 30:50.231
Do you want to see my tattoo?

30:50.320 --> 30:52.276
You've got a tattoo?

30:53.440 --> 30:55.351
Oh, fantastic!

30:55.440 --> 30:57.237
It's a gecko.

30:57.320 --> 30:58.639
I had it done last week.

30:58.720 --> 31:00.870
You're amazing, you know that?

31:00.960 --> 31:02.916
Tattoos, wacky baccy.

31:03.000 --> 31:05.150
Unbelievable.

31:05.240 --> 31:08.789
You're not at all like what you seem.
Whereas me...

31:08.880 --> 31:10.791
You can be whoever you want.

31:10.880 --> 31:14.077
No-one here knows you, except
Pete and Jenny.

31:14.160 --> 31:17.357
If you don't like who you are,
become someone else.

31:17.440 --> 31:20.352
What, and invent a life?
- Live a lie.

31:20.440 --> 31:23.955
Yeah, well. I wouldn't be
the only one doing that.

31:26.400 --> 31:27.469
What?

31:28.840 --> 31:33.072
If I tell you, promise not to breathe
a word of this to anyone.

31:33.160 --> 31:34.434
Yeah.

31:36.080 --> 31:38.514
We tell her. She has a right to know.

31:38.600 --> 31:40.875
I promised Pete I wouldn't. You promised me.

31:40.960 --> 31:43.030
We're meant to be her friends.

31:43.120 --> 31:45.190
We're meant to be Pete's, too.

31:45.280 --> 31:47.555
They have got to sort this out between them.

31:47.640 --> 31:49.870
How can they, if she doesn't know?

31:49.960 --> 31:52.269
We act like nothing has happened.

31:52.360 --> 31:54.271
Perfectly normal, OK?

31:54.360 --> 31:55.634
Karen, OK?

32:13.040 --> 32:16.828
After the Foreign Legion,
I was bodyguard to a sultan.

32:16.920 --> 32:19.753
He was assassinated.
- Yeah, it was my day off.

32:19.840 --> 32:22.798
We're not married.
Karen's my personal assistant.

32:22.880 --> 32:24.029
And masseuse.

32:24.120 --> 32:25.838
And helicopter pilot.

32:25.920 --> 32:28.593
The year after school, I made a million.

32:28.680 --> 32:32.150
The year after, he lost it.
- The year after that, I made it back.

32:38.920 --> 32:40.876
Come on. Come on.

32:42.360 --> 32:44.828
It's easier the second time round.

32:56.880 --> 32:59.474
You've got to tell her.
- No, she's happy.

32:59.560 --> 33:00.834
She's drunk.
- No.

33:00.920 --> 33:03.718
Adam.
- Rach, hi.

33:03.800 --> 33:06.917
You made it, then.
- Just. They wouldn't let me in.

33:07.000 --> 33:11.198
I said you were my husband. - You want
to hear the shite we've been saying.

33:11.280 --> 33:13.111
Thanks for coming, Karen.
- OK.

33:13.200 --> 33:15.191
How's it been going?

33:15.280 --> 33:17.635
So far, so good.

33:17.720 --> 33:19.756
I think I'll get some drinks.

33:21.160 --> 33:23.071
Ah, Mr Turnbull.

33:23.160 --> 33:25.879
Teacher?
- Tosser.

33:25.960 --> 33:28.269
Oh, God, you have to meet this guy.

33:41.240 --> 33:46.075
You know how they say you never
forget a good teacher? This is...

33:46.160 --> 33:47.639
Erm...

33:47.720 --> 33:51.838
Malcolm Chacksfield.
You still haven't lost your sense of humour.

33:51.920 --> 33:54.070
You always could make me laugh.

33:54.160 --> 33:55.878
Usually when I marked his essays.

34:00.920 --> 34:02.911
Karen, give us some of that.

34:03.000 --> 34:05.434
I'm that dehydrated, I can't even pee.

34:05.520 --> 34:07.431
Are you having a good time?

34:07.520 --> 34:10.273
Mmm. Yeah, I'm having a laugh actually.

34:10.360 --> 34:12.271
Do you know what?

34:12.360 --> 34:15.431
In this hall, Pete and I had our first kiss.

34:15.520 --> 34:17.431
Did you?

34:17.520 --> 34:20.637
With tongues. We were lashing at each other.

34:20.719 --> 34:25.873
15 years ago. That's how long
we've been together. I can't believe it.

34:28.280 --> 34:30.110
Quite an achievement, really.

34:30.199 --> 34:32.156
Jen.

34:33.280 --> 34:37.034
If your friend's husband was having an
affair, would you tell her?

34:38.480 --> 34:40.391
Er... Yeah.

34:40.480 --> 34:42.835
Yeah. God, yeah. If you're a mate.

34:42.920 --> 34:44.876
Definitely.

34:44.960 --> 34:47.155
I'll be back for a dance.
I'm going for a slash.

34:48.360 --> 34:50.315
Jen!

34:51.840 --> 34:55.196
Mr Chacksfield is why I did computing.
- You teach computing?

34:55.280 --> 34:58.636
English, and it's Malcolm.
You make me feel old.

34:58.720 --> 35:00.870
I'm old, so you must be...

35:00.960 --> 35:04.396
45.
- Is that all? When we were at school...

35:04.480 --> 35:06.948
I was still young.
I just seemed ancient to you.

35:07.040 --> 35:08.951
Adam? Adam?

35:09.040 --> 35:10.359
Where's Pete?

35:10.440 --> 35:12.431
I don't know. Having a slash?

35:12.520 --> 35:15.159
Er... I'll start with you, then.

35:15.240 --> 35:17.151
Please, outside.

35:23.360 --> 35:25.669
Karen should never have told you.

35:25.760 --> 35:27.671
No, Adam, you should have!

35:27.760 --> 35:30.354
I promised Pete I'd keep it to myself.

35:30.440 --> 35:32.271
So you tell Karen!

35:32.360 --> 35:35.113
Advertising?
Would I know any adverts you worked on?

35:35.200 --> 35:39.990
I should bloody well hope so. We've got a
big campaign with a skateboarding nun.

35:40.080 --> 35:41.638
I don't watch a lot of TV.

35:41.720 --> 35:43.392
It's on billboards.

35:43.480 --> 35:45.232
I don't get out much.

35:47.080 --> 35:48.991
I'll rip his throat out!

35:49.080 --> 35:50.559
You do not want to do that.

35:50.640 --> 35:53.598
Yes, I do! The bastard's having an affair!

35:53.680 --> 35:56.672
Yeah. And why do you think he's doing that?

36:23.400 --> 36:25.436
Do you love him?
- Shut up!

36:26.920 --> 36:30.879
Yeah!
- He doesn't know that.

36:30.960 --> 36:34.635
If you confront him, I'm telling you
it will destroy your marriage.

36:34.720 --> 36:37.632
What if he stops seeing her?
- What will make him do that?

36:37.720 --> 36:40.712
I am. If he doesn't,
you can rip his throat out.

36:40.800 --> 36:42.313
I'll hold him down.

36:43.880 --> 36:45.791
I feel sick, Adam.

36:45.880 --> 36:47.836
I feel sick.

36:51.720 --> 36:54.359
Hey, Karen, do you want to dance?

36:54.440 --> 36:56.396
Yeah. Not with you.

37:00.320 --> 37:02.231
Hiya, love.

37:04.720 --> 37:06.233
I want to go home.
- In a minute.

37:06.320 --> 37:08.276
Now.

37:10.840 --> 37:14.037
When are you working late
at the office again?

37:14.120 --> 37:17.078
Monday. I hope you haven't said anything.

37:17.160 --> 37:19.230
No, but if you carry on, I will.

37:19.320 --> 37:21.231
It's over, Pete. Dump her.

37:21.320 --> 37:24.392
You can't tell me what to do.
- Give me your word. I'm serious.

37:24.480 --> 37:26.914
I'm telling Jenny.
Do you want to wreck your marriage?

37:27.000 --> 37:29.309
Only see your kid at the weekends?

37:29.400 --> 37:31.516
Tell Amy it's finished, Pete.

37:34.160 --> 37:36.116
I'm off.

37:37.400 --> 37:39.356
I think I'll go, too.

37:41.640 --> 37:43.312
Have you seen Rach?

37:44.640 --> 37:46.596
She's dancing over there.

37:57.960 --> 38:01.396
I turn my back and she cops off
with my teacher!

38:01.480 --> 38:05.632
They were hardly copping off.
They were dancing together.

38:05.720 --> 38:07.995
He asked her out.

38:08.080 --> 38:10.036
And she accepted?

38:10.920 --> 38:11.989
Why not?

38:12.080 --> 38:15.914
He was my teacher! It's indecent.
Besides, what about Danny?

38:16.000 --> 38:18.833
I finished with him. A few days ago.

38:18.920 --> 38:21.832
What did you do that for? I liked Danny.

38:21.920 --> 38:25.799
You didn't.
You'd just rather I saw Danny than Malcolm.

38:25.880 --> 38:28.030
Malcolm? It's Mr Chacksfield!

38:28.120 --> 38:30.031
What is going on, Rachel?

38:30.120 --> 38:32.554
One boyfriend was pre-pubescent.

38:32.640 --> 38:34.551
This one is due his bus pass.

38:34.640 --> 38:38.269
Are you trying to do all the seven ages
of man? - Do I detect a note of jealousy?

38:38.360 --> 38:39.395
No.

38:39.480 --> 38:41.391
Good.

38:41.480 --> 38:46.076
If we're friends, we can't be stupid
about who the other one sees.

38:46.160 --> 38:49.789
She has a point.
- He was my favourite teacher!

38:49.880 --> 38:52.314
When he went on about Romeo And Juliet

38:52.400 --> 38:55.437
I didn't think he'd shag my ex-girlfriend.

38:55.520 --> 38:59.672
Do you think they'll shag? - Yeah.
They're grown-ups. Him in particular.

38:59.760 --> 39:03.230
Oh, yes. Marvellous end
to a marvellous evening!

39:03.320 --> 39:06.232
Yeah. I heard about Pete.
- God.

39:06.320 --> 39:08.231
Karen said you'd told her.

39:08.320 --> 39:10.834
She said I was to keep quiet about it.

39:10.920 --> 39:12.831
Well, more than she's done.

39:12.920 --> 39:14.273
What? Did she tell Rachel?

39:14.360 --> 39:16.271
Rachel? Jenny.

39:19.680 --> 39:21.193
Hello.

39:21.280 --> 39:23.236
So, is he home?

39:23.320 --> 39:26.596
Yeah. He's early, actually.
I can't believe it.

39:26.680 --> 39:30.878
Maybe it's the lure of Carol Vorderman.
At least he's here.

39:30.960 --> 39:33.679
There will be occasions
when he does have to work late.

39:33.760 --> 39:35.671
I know.

39:35.760 --> 39:38.354
But I think it's going to be all right.

39:38.440 --> 39:40.954
I feel good. It's been really nice.

39:41.040 --> 39:43.918
You deserve it, Jen. Have a good evening.

39:44.000 --> 39:45.911
Thanks.

39:46.000 --> 39:47.353
Adam?
- Yeah.

39:47.440 --> 39:49.351
Thank you.

39:49.440 --> 39:51.112
OK.

39:51.200 --> 39:53.111
Bye.

40:00.960 --> 40:02.871
Look, there's Mum.

40:02.960 --> 40:04.916
Hiya, love. Give us a kiss.

40:10.240 --> 40:13.312
What are you doing, Ramona?
- Tidying up.

40:13.400 --> 40:14.913
If you let me.

40:15.000 --> 40:16.718
Is this yours?

40:16.800 --> 40:18.916
It's Javier's. Karen says it's
OK in my room.

40:19.000 --> 40:20.797
Is this place a crack den?

40:20.880 --> 40:23.189
Karen knows my attitude towards drugs.

40:23.280 --> 40:24.793
Drugs?

40:24.880 --> 40:27.235
- I will not tolerate them here.
- This is not drugs.

40:27.320 --> 40:29.231
Where does it end, Ramona?

40:29.320 --> 40:31.151
It starts with marijuana,

40:31.240 --> 40:34.596
and before you know, you're robbing
old ladies to pay for cocaine.

40:34.680 --> 40:35.954
This is no marijuana!

40:36.040 --> 40:37.951
You're in denial. It's a slippery slope.

40:38.040 --> 40:41.953
David, this is tobacco.
Javier likes to roll his own.

40:43.040 --> 40:44.393
So it's harmless?

40:44.480 --> 40:46.675
No, it is tobacco.

40:46.760 --> 40:48.716
It gives you cancer.

40:53.520 --> 40:55.431
So, how did your date go?

40:55.520 --> 40:57.476
With Malcolm?

40:57.560 --> 40:59.835
Yeah, with Malcolm.

41:00.320 --> 41:03.073
It didn't.
- What, he cancelled?

41:03.160 --> 41:06.072
No!
- You did?

41:06.160 --> 41:08.071
No.

41:08.160 --> 41:09.115
So?

41:10.320 --> 41:13.392
Well, I was waitlng for him in this bar...

41:25.040 --> 41:27.270
He was dressed llke a teacher.

41:27.360 --> 41:28.429
He is a teacher.

41:28.520 --> 41:31.751
It's the school holidays.
He still dresses like a teacher.

41:33.840 --> 41:38.356
You know you can tell in the first ten
seconds if there's anything there?

41:38.440 --> 41:40.590
Yeah.
- It didn't take that long.

41:40.680 --> 41:42.636
Oh. So what did you do?

41:43.680 --> 41:45.033
What could I do?

41:52.560 --> 41:55.632
<i>What, you scarpered?
- Yeah. I did a runner.</i>

41:55.720 --> 41:57.676
God! Mr Chacksfield...

42:00.200 --> 42:01.599
Poor bastard.

42:02.640 --> 42:04.596
Yeah. Poor bastard.

42:05.880 --> 42:07.836
Come on.

42:16.720 --> 42:17.914
Yeah. Hello.

42:18.000 --> 42:20.560
Hi, Jen.
- Hi.

42:20.640 --> 42:23.234
Guess what? I've got to work late tonight.

42:23.320 --> 42:25.231
Why?

42:25.320 --> 42:29.552
The computer's gone down and I've
got to process those figures for Patrick.

42:29.640 --> 42:30.993
He's got a meeting tomorrow.

42:31.080 --> 42:34.038
Er... How long are you going to be?

42:34.120 --> 42:37.032
I'll be able to leave in about 20 minutes.

42:37.120 --> 42:40.351
Er...that's if the computer behaves itself.

42:41.280 --> 42:43.191
OK.

42:43.280 --> 42:45.874
Erm, that's fine. The meal will keep.

42:45.960 --> 42:47.916
See you later, yeah?

42:48.000 --> 42:49.956
Yeah. All right. Bye.

42:51.160 --> 42:52.752
Pete, oh, listen. Will you...

42:53.800 --> 42:55.438
Damn...

43:01.320 --> 43:03.231
Hello.

43:03.320 --> 43:06.312
Pete, will you bring some wine...
- Who do you want?

43:06.400 --> 43:09.119
Sorry. Eh? Pete Gifford, please.

43:09.200 --> 43:11.794
I'm afraid he's left.
- He's left?

43:11.880 --> 43:13.677
Yeah.
- When did he leave?

43:13.760 --> 43:15.671
Half an hour ago.

43:15.760 --> 43:17.671
Right.

43:17.760 --> 43:20.957
Er... OK.
- Sorry.

43:21.040 --> 43:22.996
Yeah. Thanks.

43:27.400 --> 43:30.358
Why did you break a confidence?
- Adam broke it first.

43:30.440 --> 43:31.634
That doesn't excuse you.

43:31.720 --> 43:34.871
I don't need excusing.
I was being open and honest.

43:34.960 --> 43:37.076
Open and honest?

43:37.160 --> 43:39.230
Yes! Not that I expect thanks.

43:39.320 --> 43:42.357
I realise they're not qualities
people put much store by.

43:42.440 --> 43:44.351
What are you talking about?

43:44.440 --> 43:47.716
I can't stand hypocrisy.
Our whole bloody lives are a fraud.

43:47.800 --> 43:51.315
We spend time with people we don't like
and lie to those we do!

43:51.400 --> 43:53.470
You don't like Pete and Jenny?

43:53.560 --> 43:58.031
Yes, I do like them. I'm talking about
James and Natasha and Mark and Laura.

43:59.200 --> 44:02.158
Well...I don't really like them, either.

44:02.960 --> 44:05.599
So let's just tell them
we don't want to see them any more.

44:05.680 --> 44:08.240
That's not very nice.
- Who cares about being nice?

44:08.320 --> 44:09.275
I do!

44:09.360 --> 44:12.955
So once a month we have to sit there
and pretend we want to be there?

44:14.120 --> 44:17.192
If the alternative is your brand of honesty,
then, yeah.

44:18.440 --> 44:20.158
Hello.
- Hello, David.

44:20.240 --> 44:22.549
James. We were talking about you.

44:22.640 --> 44:24.676
Can you do dinner next Friday?

44:24.760 --> 44:26.796
Dinner next Friday? Erm...

44:28.880 --> 44:31.235
Oh, right...it's a bit difficult.

44:31.320 --> 44:33.914
Erm...
- How about Saturday?

44:34.000 --> 44:36.309
Saturday's no easier, I'm afraid.

44:36.400 --> 44:39.358
The week after?
- No, nor the following week.

44:39.440 --> 44:41.351
That's a shame.

44:41.440 --> 44:44.716
I tell you what,
why don't I call you when we're a bit freer?

44:44.800 --> 44:47.633
OK. I'll leave it up to you.
- OK. Bye.

44:49.880 --> 44:52.599
Well, that wasn't very honest, was it?

44:54.120 --> 44:56.076
Do you want to come in?

44:57.120 --> 45:00.078
No, I'm trying to avoid Karen at the minute.

45:00.160 --> 45:01.559
Oh, yeah.

45:05.840 --> 45:07.751
Well, that was nice.

45:07.840 --> 45:09.796
Yeah, Rach, it was.

45:11.520 --> 45:13.670
It shows that we can be friends.

45:13.760 --> 45:16.194
Going to the cinema, seeing a film...

45:16.280 --> 45:18.350
Arguing about it afterwards.

45:18.440 --> 45:20.351
Talking about who we've been seeing.

45:20.440 --> 45:22.874
You did most of the talking there.

45:24.320 --> 45:27.392
I think we can make this friends thing work.

45:33.160 --> 45:35.116
Well...

45:41.400 --> 45:43.391
I'll see you, then.

45:43.480 --> 45:45.436
I'll see you.

46:20.480 --> 46:22.630
See you at work tomorrow, then.

46:22.720 --> 46:27.396
Yeah, but it might be a good idea
if I didn't come round for a couple of days.

46:31.440 --> 46:33.954
Don't put yourself out on my account.

46:38.480 --> 46:41.358
Hiya, Jen.
- Hello, Peter.

46:41.440 --> 46:43.476
Your son wanted to say hello.

46:49.120 --> 46:50.473
There you go.

46:53.520 --> 46:54.635
Go on.

46:57.560 --> 46:59.596
Now let's see how you like it.

